**37.** If Tk. $3,000$ is invested at $10\%$ profit and Tk. $2,000$ is invested at $8\%$ profit, what will be the average profit rate on the total principal?<br>
[37th BCS Preli] + [Directorate of Food (Various Posts)-2020] + [SPCBL-(AM)-2023]

* a. 9%
* b. `9.2%`
* c. 8%
* d. 8.2%

+++ Solution:
- $\text{Profit from Tk. 3000} = (3000 \times 10) / 100 = 300$
- $\text{Profit from Tk. 2000} = (2000 \times 8) / 100 = 160$
- $\text{Total Capital} = 3000 + 2000 = 5000$
- $\text{Total Profit} = 3000 \times \frac{10}{100} + 2000 \times \frac{8}{100} = 300 + 160 = 460$
- $\text{Average Profit Rate} = (460 \times 100) / 5000 = 9.2\%$
+++

